// Semantic direction:
// adaptiv_optimalisering continuously improves running programs based on observed behavior.
// rt_hotspot identifies frequently executed functions and loops that are worth optimizing.
// profileringspunkt is a lightweight instrumentation site embedded during compilation.
// forutsetning_registrer records a speculative assumption made during optimization.
// forutsetning_ugyldiggjør fires when runtime evidence contradicts an assumption, triggering recompilation.
// forutsetning_konfidensterskel controls how many observations are needed before committing to a specialization.
// online_kompilering runs the optimizing compiler on a background kompilerings_tråd while the program continues.
// async_kompilering installs optimized code atomically when it's ready, without pausing execution.
// type_spesialisering_rt specializes a function for the types observed at each call site.
// polimorft_inline_cache stores the last N observed receiver types and their method addresses.
// pic_invalidér clears the cache when a new, unseen type appears (megamorft site).
// sløyfe_tile_rt optimizes loop tile sizes based on cache hit rates observed during profiling.
// vektoriserings_bredde_rt adjusts SIMD lane count based on the actual data alignment seen.
// parallellisering_rt decides the optimal tråd_antall based on current CPU utilization.
// escape_analyse_rt refines compile-time analysis with runtime evidence to enable stack_promotering.
// prefetching_rt inserts memory prefetch instructions tuned to observed allokeringsmønster.
// degradering_deteksjon triggers re_optimalisering when throughput drops below ytelse_mål.
// bayesiansk_optimalisering_aro models the objective function and picks hyperparameters efficiently.
// multi_armed_bandit balances utforskning (trying new configs) vs utnytting (using the best known).

// Primitive flow:
// hotspot deteksjon: teller_utførelse[funksjon] > hotspot_terskel
//   -> async_kompilering(funksjon, profil_data)
//   -> installer optimalisert versjon atomisk
// type_spesialisering: kall_sted observert: alltid type A (pic_monomorft)
//   -> forutsetning_registrer({kall_sted, type: A})
//   -> kompilér spesialisert versjon for type A + guard
//   ny type B observerer: forutsetning_ugyldiggjør -> pic_polymorft -> re-optimaliser
// sløyfe_tile adaptasjon: mål cache-miss rate per tile_størrelse
//   bayesiansk_optimalisering: neste tile_størrelse = argmax(forventet_forbedring)
//   -> mål ytelse -> oppdater modell -> konvergér mot optimal
// self_tuning JVM-stil: monitorér mål_latens -> degradering_detektert?
//   re_optimalisering: prøv nye hyperparametere -> sammenlign -> behold beste

// This defines adaptive runtime optimization: hotspot profiling, speculative specialization
// with invalidation, online compilation, adaptive loop tiling, escape analysis refinement,
// and Bayesian self-tuning.
